com.viaoa.process

Class OACron

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.viaoa.process.OACron

  • public abstract class OACron
extends Object
    Used to define and find the next time a Cron-like entry should be ran. * * * * command to be executed - - - - - | | | | | | | | | +----- day of week (0-6) (Sunday=0) - Java: 1-7 (Sunday=1) | | | +---------- month (1-12) - Java: 0-11 | | +-------------- day of month (1-31), also allows "last" | +-------------------- hour (0 - 23) +-------------------------- min (0 - 59) Each field needs to be separate by space or tab. Field values can use a single number, "-" for a range, and commas to separate more then one. see OACronProcessor# to register cron to be processed
    Author:
    vvia
